newsArticles.title: NASA's Big Moon Robot Trip
newsArticles.summary: On January 8, NASA is going to send a cool robot to the Moon! It will land there on February 23, and you can watch it on TV from January 4.

newsArticles.title: NASA's Spacecraft Visits a Fiery Moon
newsArticles.summary: NASA's spaceship called Juno is going to visit Jupiter's fiery moon Io on December 30. It's the closest visit in over 20 years!

newsArticles.title: Space Telescope Sees a Faraway Planet
newsArticles.summary: A big space camera called the James Webb Space Telescope took a picture of a faraway planet named Uranus. It's really pretty with rings and stormy spots!

newsArticles.title: Webb: The Super Space Camera
newsArticles.summary: Webb is a very special space camera that can see far, far into space. It's like a superhero camera because it learned from older space cameras!

newsArticles.title: NASA's Big Space Phone is 60 Years Old!
newsArticles.summary: NASA has a big space phone called the Deep Space Network. It talks to spaceships and is 60 years old now. It's getting better to talk to more spaceships!

latestNews.title: Night Sky Show at NASA's Space Center
latestNews.summary: On February 22, 2023, people saw the moon smiling and two bright stars, Jupiter and Venus, in the sky over NASA's place where they build spaceships.
